id: jf-644n
title: Replace YAML-like output with official TOON serialization
description: "The default output path is labeled TOON but uses a bespoke YAML-like envelope rather than the official Token-Oriented Object Notation implementation requested by the project contract. Adopt the current official @toon-format/toon encoder, preserve typed envelopes and redaction, validate lossless decode/schema behavior, and update every user/agent document and compatibility test."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[5]: agents,format,output,serialization,toon
created_at: "2026-07-23T04:53:59.365Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:23:15.225Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T05:22:11.979Z"
author: codex-jellyfin
estimated_minutes: 360
acceptance_criteria: All toon output is encoded with the latest compatible official @toon-format/toon package; Every emitted document round-trips through the official decoder to the exact JSON data model; Redaction and typed envelope semantics remain intact across all formatter helpers; README and docs distinguish TOON from YAML and show valid current syntax; Bun and npm lockfiles are reproducible and audited; Actual jf-cli read-only live commands validate TOON output without persisting private data
definition_of_ready: Official package API and types verified from installed node_modules; duplicate-safe PM search completed; live server read-only mode available.
goal: jf-mqpo
value: "Make the default agent format genuinely compact, interoperable, and standards-based."
impact: Corrects the central LLM-facing output contract across every command without altering Jellyfin data.
outcome: Official TOON v4 serialization is the default validated output for all CLI commands.
why_now: The current default contradicts the explicit project requirement and blocks trustworthy agent/programmatic workflows.
parent: jf-gn5j
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
reporter: codex-jellyfin
severity: high
repro_steps: Run jf-cli --format toon on a uniform list; observe YAML list syntax without TOON array counts or field headers. Compare with @toon-format/toon encode output and official specification fixtures.
resolution: "Replaced the bespoke YAML-like encoder with @toon-format/toon 4.0.0; canonicalized formatter envelopes and schema fields; routed validation, diagnostics, errors, and read-only failures through official TOON; added direct decoder/schema contracts and live compiled CLI proof."
expected_result: Default and explicit toon output is standards-conformant TOON generated by the official package and losslessly decodes to the intended typed envelope.
actual_result: "The formatter manually emits YAML-like text and documentation calls TOON YAML, so external TOON decoders cannot rely on the output contract."
affected_version: 2026.7.21-3
fixed_version: next release
component: formatters
regression: false
customer_impact: "Agents lose the token-efficiency, schema guardrails, and interoperable validation promised by the default format; programmatic consumers can mistake YAML for TOON."
