comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:53:59.365Z",codex-jellyfin,"Official sources reviewed on 2026-07-23: toon-format/toon is the reference TypeScript implementation and @toon-format/toon 4.0.0 is the current npm release; the published spec describes lossless JSON-model encoding with explicit array lengths and tabular headers."
  "2026-07-23T05:08:43.852Z",codex-jellyfin,"Implemented official @toon-format/toon 4.0.0 encoding/decoding, normalized canonical formatter type names and descriptive fields to the JSON Schema registry, fixed error/read-only bypass output, added direct decode-to-schema contract coverage, refreshed agent/TOON docs, and advanced the release tooling pin to pm CLI 2026.7.22. Unit suite: 915 pass, 177 live skips, 0 fail; typecheck/lint/file-length pass."
  "2026-07-23T05:21:56.046Z",codex-jellyfin,"Acceptance evidence: PM-linked suite 10/10 passes; 915 Bun tests pass with 177 expected non-live skips; portable Vitest 906/906 passes; full compiled read-only Jellyfin E2E 177/177 passes; real system/users/items/sessions/libraries/tasks TOON output decodes and validates against canonical schemas; connection/auth/OpenAPI/all-format diagnostics pass; tracked and history secret scans pass."
  "2026-07-23T05:23:15.216Z",codex-jellyfin,"Release tooling verification: npm registry latest pm-changelog is 2026.7.22; project-managed extension upgraded from 2026.7.18 to 2026.7.22 and activated successfully through pm CLI 2026.7.22."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T04:53:59.365Z",codex-jellyfin,Do not replace TOON with YAML aliases or a home-grown encoder. Use top-level imports from the installed official package and inspect its bundled type declarations before implementation.
  "2026-07-23T05:08:44.744Z",codex-jellyfin,"Design decision: TOON is now a distinct standards-backed wire format. YAML remains separately supported; schema auto-detection tries JSON, strict TOON, then YAML. Empty arrays, nulls, and false values are preserved because removing them changes output semantics and breaks schema contracts."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T05:21:55.205Z",codex-jellyfin,Text-pattern tests are not sufficient for a structured wire format. Decode output with the official implementation and assert the semantic envelope so quoting and tabular compaction changes do not create false failures.
